1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:07,520
The museum was inaugurated on November 1, 1982. It was built in the Kruria Castle,

2
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:13,920
on the left side of its entrance. The architects of the museum were Pranvra Hoja and Piro Veso.

3
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:19,600
The museum was built in Kruria because it was the centre of the Albanian resistance

4
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,640
against the Ottomans in the 15th century, and its name was well known all across Europe.

5
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:37,200
Three sieges, 1450, 1466, 1467, failed and the Ottoman conquered the castle only in 1478.

6
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:41,040
The museum building has the character of a memorial.

7
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:46,240
In the architectural exterior, two main volumes are distinguished,

8
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:50,160
the extended horizontal part with the main halls and the vertical one built

9
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:55,840
similar to the northern typical colours. The interior is arranged so as the spaces

10
00:00:55,840 --> 00:01:01,040
are combined successively, without interruption, according to the concept of the presentation of

11
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:08,400
history. History, architecture and art are perceived as one. Elements such as heavy beams

12
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:16,160
and stone arches are used. Artwork, stone carvings, wood carvings, iron, graphics, glass paintings,

13
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:21,440
play the role of supplementary historical material. As you enter the museum you will

14
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:25,680
find a sculptural group that presents George Castrioti in the middle of his people.

15
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:32,640
The warriors are not named. Their garments and headdresses demonstrate the participation of

16
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:37,600
all regions in the war. The woman figure shows her participation in battles.

17
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:42,960
Janak Pa O and Jain Kajdari are the authors of this one.

